Package: depCenR
Title: Bagging-MME for Dependently Censored Survival Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Hyun-Soo",
           family = "Zhang",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "hszhang@yuhs.ac",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4973-9792"))
Description: Implements the Bootstrap-Aggregated Method-of-Moments Estimation
    (Bagging-MME) framework for estimating correlation (Kendall's tau) and
    marginal distributions from dependently censored survival data. Provides
    functions for dependence testing ('depTest'), dependence estimation with
    confidence intervals ('depEst'), and augmented estimation for small samples
    using diffusion-model-based data augmentation ('depEst.aug'). The underlying
    model assumes bivariate generalized-gamma marginals linked by a Clayton
    copula, with global optimization performed via Generalized Simulated
    Annealing (GenSA) across partitioned dependence-parameter sub-ranges.
